content:
Update your root email address by directly logging in to the AWS console as a root user. 

This task applies to this telephony model.

SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH AMAZON CONNECT	SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY FROM AMAZON CONNECT	SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY

In the AWS Console, log in as a root user.
To get to the My Security Credentials page, choose your account name or number from the interface in the upper right corner of the console, and then click Security Credentials.
To get to the Update account settings page, select Edit account name, email, and password from the options next to Account details.
To update fields, select Edit and enter your changes.

If the email address update fails, log a support ticket with Salesforce Customer Support.

When a root email address has changed, and you canâ€™t access the AWS Console using your previous root email address, contact Salesforce Customer Support to reset your root email address.
title: Update AWS Root Email Address in Service Cloud
